.docname {Live Room Overview}
.include {docs}

Once you have logged in and selected your organization's domain, the **Dashboard** serves as your primary command center for real-time analytics.

The dashboard has two distinct views you can switch between at any time using the toggle in the top-left corner:
- **List view** — a live data table showing every room at a glance (this page).
- **Graph view** — time-series charts and sensor simulation controls (see [Analytics Graphs](page-7.qd)).

---

## 🎛️ Dashboard Controls

At the top of the dashboard you will find three controls:

1. **View toggle (top-left):** Switch between the List and Graph views.
2. **Clock & Date (centre):** Displays the current time and date, confirming you are looking at live data.
3. **Building selector (top-right):** Switch between different buildings in your current domain. The table and graphs update instantly when you change buildings.

A **Fullscreen icon** also appears at the top — see Focus Mode below.

---

## 📊 The Room Statistics Table

The core of the List view is the live data table. It automatically updates to show real-time metrics for every room in the selected building.

| Column | What it means |
| :--- | :--- |
| **Room** | The unique identifier or name of the room. |
| **Status** | A quick-read text indicator of how full the room is. |
| **Teacher** | The staff member currently scheduled for that room (if applicable). |
| **Temp** | The current live temperature reading from the room's sensor. |
| **People** | The real-time occupant count detected by the room's sensors. |
| **Capacity** | The maximum allowed number of occupants for safety and comfort. |

---

## 🚦 Occupancy Status Indicators

CrowdVision automatically calculates an occupancy status based on the percentage of the room's capacity that is currently filled.

* 🟢 **Empty** — 0% occupancy.
* 🔵 **Normal** — 1% to 50% occupancy.
* 🟠 **Crowded** — 51% to 95% occupancy.
* 🔴 **Full** — 96% to 100% occupancy.
* 🚨 **Overcrowded** — over 100% occupancy. Requires immediate attention.

---

## 📺 Focus Mode (Fullscreen)

If you are setting up CrowdVision on a dedicated display — such as in a lobby, corridor, or security control room — use Focus Mode.

**How to activate:**
1. Click the **Fullscreen icon** (expand arrows) at the top of the dashboard.
2. The interface hides the side navigation and top bar, expanding the data table to fill the entire screen.
3. Text is automatically scaled up for readability from a distance.

> 💡 **To exit:** Press `Esc` or click the Fullscreen icon again.
